## Refactoring: Declare Scope Before Touching Anything

The biggest AI refactoring risk: the agent "improves" unrelated things and breaks callers.

```
Refactor [function/hook/component] in @[exact file].

Goal: [what it should look like after]

Preserve EXACTLY:
- Function signature: [describe signature]
- Return type: [describe]
- Error handling behavior

Do NOT:
- Modify any file that imports from this path
- Change the public API
- Add new functionality
- Rename exports

Make changes file by file. Show me each diff before moving to the next.
```

**Real example:**
```
Refactor the createClient function in @lib/supabase/server.ts to use 
the latest @supabase/ssr createServerClient API.

Preserve EXACTLY:
- Export name: createClient
- It must remain an async function
- Cookie handling must still work in Next.js App Router

Do NOT touch:
- lib/supabase/client.ts (browser client — completely separate)
- lib/supabase/middleware.ts
- Any component that imports createClient

Show me ONLY the change to server.ts. I will review before you continue.
```

