## The plan.md Pattern (For Complex Features)

For any feature touching 3+ files, create a plan first:

```
// In a fresh chat or Claude.ai — design before you build:

Design a [feature] for a Rocket.new Next.js + Supabase project.
Stack: Next.js App Router, TypeScript, Supabase (@supabase/ssr), Tailwind, Netlify.

Produce plan.md with:
1. Database tables and columns needed
2. RLS policies
3. New files to create (with full paths)
4. Implementation phases (Phase 1 = data layer, Phase 2 = UI, Phase 3 = integrations)
5. What must NOT be changed in existing files

No code yet — only the plan.
```

Then in Cursor:
```
Implement Phase 1 from @plan.md: [phase description]
Do not implement Phase 2 yet. I will review Phase 1 before we continue.
```

