## Context Management

### Start a fresh chat when:
- Switching from debugging to building a new feature
- The conversation has 15+ exchanges (context degradation is measurable by this point)
- Agent went off-rails and you've reverted — don't correct in the same chat, start fresh
- Moving to a completely different part of the codebase

### Always open a new chat with:
```
Rocket.new Next.js TypeScript project.
Stack: Next.js App Router, Supabase (@supabase/ssr), Stripe, Tailwind, Netlify.
Task: [exactly what you're doing this session]
Relevant files: @[file1] @[file2]
Constraint: [what must not change]
```

### What NOT to include:
- Files unrelated to the current task (they dilute attention)
- The entire codebase when 2-3 files are enough
- Old conversation history when starting a new task

